-- Japan’s April LNG Imports Rise 14.9%; Oil Purchases Gain 12.9%
-- B y   J a c o b   A d e l m a n
-- 2012-05-23T02:20:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-23/japan-s-april-lng-imports-rise-14-9-oil-purchases-gain-12-9-.html
Japan ’s liquefied natural gas imports
rose 14.9 percent in April from a year earlier while crude
purchases advanced 12.9 percent, according to the  finance
ministry .  LNG shipments from overseas climbed to 6.91 million metric
tons, the ministry said in a preliminary report today. Imports
of crude were 19.16 million kiloliters, or 4 million barrels a
day, the data showed.  Utilities increased thermal power output by 45 percent in
April to compensate for a drop in nuclear generation, according
to  data  released May 16 by the Federation of Electric Power
Companies of Japan. The average utilization rate for atomic
plants was at 2 percent in the month, down from 51 percent a
year earlier.  The following table shows Japan’s imports of crude, oil
products, gas and coal for April:  
Note: Crude oil and gasoline are in millions of kiloliters. LNG,
